reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect replacement for my AIO
reviews.reviewText: My AIO H100i went bad for my 2011 LGA Asus Rampage IV Black edition so I ordered this to replace it. Installation was really easy in my opinion. I did need to remove the processor completely (to provide room for one of the spacers) and I realized that the backplate provided isn't needed for this CPU type as it has its own that works. Instructions were accurate and easy to read; just pay attention to the orientation of everything. Bags were also labeled with the CPU type which was helpful.CPU temp is honestly better than it was with the radiator. I'm running a cool 30 C right now with my i7 4930K.One thing, if you get the RGB, be sure your mobo has a ARGB 5v 3pin port; otherwise you can't hook up the light. But, at least the lights are optional so I just left that part unplugged.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great cooler so far - Very Hard to Install.
reviews.reviewText: Running a Ryzen 7 5700G and it keeps my temps at 40-50C. Not the easiest to install. Make sure you dig out your old plastic clip mounting hardware that came with the mother board. lucky i didn't throw mine away. Beware its a very tight fit onto the motherboard. so if you aren't comfortable using a little bit of force then i wouldn't recommend this cooler for you. I also forgot to mention i took my motherboard out of my case to install. It would of been way harder if i would have left it in the case(Zalman S2 ATX Mid Tower).

reviews.reviewerName: 50 Shades of Beige50 Shades of Beige
reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Unique design, a little loud but it's worth it.
reviews.reviewText: Original review: This cooler looks unique and does a decent job of cooling my R5 1600X. I can run 3.8Ghz on all cores and average around 75C with an aggressive fan curve during a synthetic stress test. It both looks and sounds like a turbine engine when it spins up. If you keep fans below 50% the noise is negligible. This is a tall cooler. I would not recommend it for SFF builds. There are probably better performing coolers for the price, but I'm paying for the somewhat unique look, and I'm okay with that.Update: Be mindful of the height of this cooler, it is too tall for most of the really cheap Mid-Towers like DIYPC S2-BK or the ones common on Ali. It fits snugly in a Dell Optiplex 3020 M/T.The cooler also performs well with my R7 2700. I run 4.2 Ghz at ~1.3V on all cores comfortably.

reviews.reviewerName: robert l von hadenrobert l von haden
reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This cooler works with a wide variety of cpus. My socket 1366 went from 70 C down to 48 C
reviews.reviewText: The installation of this CPU cooler was amazing. I used one for my socekt 1366 motherboard. I was using the stock cooler and my temperatures were about 70 C depending on load. Now after replacing the stock cooler, the temperature is almost 20 C cooler. If you are looking for a decent CPU cooler that will not break the bank, I HIGHLY recommend this cooler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cool solution for X99 boards
reviews.reviewText: If you're looking to build up a dual socket X99 machine with LGA 2011 socket CPUS, these are the way to go. These coolers are very quiet and keep the Haswell 2699 chip 72-cores under 30 degrees C. They are single fan, so these coolers are compact and a nice fit on the X99 boards from Machinist, etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works well but difficult to install
reviews.reviewText: Works really well, looks awesome, quiet. Took 1 star off because it is ABSURDLY difficult to install. I bought 2 at the same time, and thought once I installed one the other would be easy...NOPE. the clips are extremely difficult to connect properly, and took a lot more force/strength than any other fan I've ever installed. I was seriously afraid I was going to break my motherboard and processor... But, once you finally get it on there, it works great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Is a very good CPU cooler, an looks awesome especially lit up, but because of it's round design makes extremely hard to get the clips to mount, but can be done..

reviews.reviewTitle: I read the warnings but I did not heed them
reviews.reviewText: The heatsink is fine, looks nice, works fine yada yada, but HOLY CRAP IT IS SO BIG, it is a PIG to fit into any PC unless you have a completely barren motherboard, at almost any angle it would hit the motherboard shrouds or my gpu,this thing was a MAJOR PAIN to get installed

This replaced the stock cooler on my I7 4790k when the mounting bracket failed. It was very hard to install on a MSI Gaming series G Motherboard due to the height of the heat sinks on the CPU power ICs, had to remove them then reinstall afterward. The force required to clip it to the mounting ring was worrying as well. On the other hand, 2 fans a (static blue) LED, included HS paste, shroud, quiet operation and considerably cooler temps than I had on the stock cooler make it a great deal.

reviews.reviewTitle: Looks and works good but painful install
reviews.reviewText: Good- pretty quite even under load,leds are super brightKeeps my i5 8400 at 100% load under 60c at just 50% fanbest cooler for the price (besides amd stock)Bad- mounting system is awful, if you ever plan on switching cpus get something elseIf you have a large gpu backplate it may not fit
